
msgctxt "LHS.030_Tools.subj"
msgid "Tools"
msgstr ""

msgid "Tools\\wh#\n\\C="
msgstr ""

msgid "You can use the following tools to fill rooms in your level:"
msgstr ""

msgid "\\0\n   Wall\\h#"
msgstr ""

msgid "The wall tool can be used to place walls."
msgstr ""

msgid "\\1\n   Background\\h#"
msgstr ""

msgid "The background tool can be used to place backgrounds."
msgstr ""

msgid "\\2\n   Spike\\h#"
msgstr ""

msgid "The spike tool can be used to place spikes. You can use the expand subtool to\nplace spikes on a surface with one click (or slide)."
msgstr ""

msgid "\\3\n   Trinket\\h#"
msgstr ""

msgid "The trinket tool can be used to place trinkets. Please note that there is a limit\nof twenty trinkets in a level."
msgstr ""

msgid "\\4\n   Checkpoint\\h#"
msgstr ""

msgid "The checkpoint tool can be used to place checkpoints."
msgstr ""

msgid "\\5\n   Disappearing platform\\h#"
msgstr ""

msgid "The disappearing platform tool can be used to place disappearing platforms."
msgstr ""

msgid "\\6\n   Conveyor\\h#"
msgstr ""

msgid "The conveyor tool can be used to place conveyors."
msgstr ""

msgid "\\7\n   Moving platform\\h#"
msgstr ""

msgid "The moving platform tool can be used to place moving platforms."
msgstr ""

msgid "\\8\n   Enemy\\h#"
msgstr ""

msgid "The enemy tool can be used to place enemies. The shape and color of the enemy are\ndetermined by the enemy type setting and the tileset (color) respectively."
msgstr ""

msgid "\\9\n   Gravity line\\h#"
msgstr ""

msgid "The gravity line tool can be used to place gravity lines."
msgstr ""

msgid "\\^0\n   Roomtext\\h#"
msgstr ""

msgid "The roomtext tool can be used to place text."
msgstr ""

msgid "\\^1\n   Terminal\\h#"
msgstr ""

msgid "The terminal tool can be used to place terminals. First place the terminal, then\ntype a name for the script. For more information about scripting, please refer to\nthe scripting references."
msgstr ""

msgid "\\^2\n   Script box\\h#"
msgstr ""

msgid "The script box tool can be used to place script boxes. First click on the top left\ncorner, then on the bottom right corner, then type a name for the script. For more\ninformation about scripting, please refer to the scripting references."
msgstr ""

msgid "\\^3\n   Warp token\\h#"
msgstr ""

msgid "The warp token tool can be used to place warp tokens. First click where the\nentrance should be, then where the exit should be."
msgstr ""

msgid "\\^4\n   Warp line\\h#"
msgstr ""

msgid "The warp line tool can be used to place warp lines. Please note that warp lines\ncan only be placed on the edges of a room."
msgstr ""

msgid "\\^5\n   Crewmate\\h#"
msgstr ""

msgid "The crewmate tool can be used to place missing crewmates that can be rescued. If\nall crewmates are rescued, the level will be finished. Please note that there is\na limit of twenty missing crewmates in a level."
msgstr ""

msgid "\\^6\n   Start point\\h#"
msgstr ""

msgid "The start point tool can be used to place the start point."
msgstr ""
